       " ['Ojos de Brujo',\n",
       "  'Ojos de Brujo (\"Sorcerer\\'s eyes\" in Spanish) was an eight-piece band from Barcelona, Spain  formed in 1998 and disbanded in 2012. The band described its style as \"hip-hop with a little flamenco\", and was comprised of guitarists Ramón and Paco, singer Marina, percussionists Xavi and Max, DJ/keyboard player Panko, drummer/percussionist Sergio, and bassist Javi.  The band received several awards, among them the Radio 3 World Music Award for Europe in 2004. <a href=\"https://www.last.fm/music/Ojos+de+Brujo\">Read more on Last.fm</a>',\n",
